A model is a derivative work of its training data. Because the upstream
Happy Whale dataset used during training is CC-BY-NC-4.0, the trained model
weights inherit that licence. We cannot relax the upstream non-commercial
restriction.

---

IMPORTANT USAGE RESTRICTIONS

The trained models in this repository were developed using datasets that
include data licensed under CC-BY-NC-4.0 (Happy Whale) and ImageNet
(non-commercial research only, via pretrained backbones such as ResNet /
EfficientNet / Vision Transformer).

As a result:

1. The trained models may NOT be used for commercial purposes without
   explicit permission from the original data providers (Happy Whale and
   the Ministry of Natural Resources of the Russian Federation).

2. This restriction applies specifically to the trained model weights
   (.pt, .pth, .onnx files) and any derivatives thereof.

3. Pretrained models (ResNet, EfficientNet, ViT, Swin) were trained on
   ImageNet, which has non-commercial research-only terms.

For full license details, see:
https://github.com/0x0000dead/whales-identification/blob/main/LICENSE_MODELS.md

For commercial licensing inquiries:
- GitHub Issues: https://github.com/0x0000dead/whales-identification/issues
- Marine mammal community datasets contact: см. LICENSE_DATA.md
